e   Rheams  .","Americanized form of German   Riehm  ."]},{"name":"Ream","meanings":["Perhaps an Americanized form of German   Riehm  ,   Rehm  , or <b>Röhm</b> (see   Roehm  ).","English: perhaps a nickname from Middle English <i>reaume</i>, <i>reame</i> ‘realm, dominion’, although the context for the adoption of this word as a surname is unclear."]}]},{"name":"Everhart","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Eberhardt   or   Everhardt   and German or Dutch   Everhard  . Compare   Averhart  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Averhart","meanings":["Variant of   Everhart  , a surname of German or Dutch origin."]},{"name":"Eberhardt","meanings":["from <i>eber</i> ‘boar’ + <i>hard</i> ‘strong, hardy’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Everhart Riehm was born in 1465, in Leimen, Amt Heidelberg, Baden, his father, Nicholeus \"Nicholas\" Riehm, was 33 and his mother, Fräulein Nicholeus Riehm, was 28. He married Fräulein Everhart Riehm in 1490, in Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1509, in Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1465–1509":"1465–1509","1470–Female":"1470–Surnud","1485–1535":"1485–1535","1490–1550":"1490–1550","1432–1490":"1432–1490","1437–Female":"1437–Surnud","1437":"1437","1535":"1535","1457":"1457","1465":"1465","1432":"1432","1485":"1485","1550":"1550","1509":"1509","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","Leimen, Heidelberg, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Leimen, Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Leimen, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Leimen, Heidelberg, Baden, Germany":"Leimen, Kreis Heidelberg, Baden, Saksamaa","of Sindelfingen, Neckarkreis, Wuerttemberg":"Sindelfingen, Kreis Böblingen, Württemberg, Saksamaa","Leiman, Heidelburg, Baden, Germany":"Baden"},"f